I’ve been pretty quiet around here lately because honestly, it’s been really rough these past few weeks balancing work and being the mom my boys need. In spite of the challenges which are so often trivial in the grand scheme of things, I’ve been been reflecting, connecting, and slowing down to be present. My youngest just started to crawl, albeit backwards, and my oldest just pedalled off on his own. Amid the challenges and the beautiful moments, I’ve been painting and making plans to expand my offerings. Thank you all for being here, for your community, and your support. More to come. 📷 @bobbydazzlerphotography 
.

A number of new big pieces are leaving my studio soon and heading to the lovely galleries I work with. The new pieces are a tribute to the incredible memories I have collected after having lived in the lower mainland of BC for over a decade. There are only a small number of new pieces and email subscribers will be notified as soon as they’re displayed. And, if big pieces aren’t in your plans, I’m beginning to shift gears and am working on a new collection celebrating transitions and transformation that highlights my new lovely home and community on Vancouver island.

Two large diptychs that will be shipping out this week. Which one of your fav? 
.
.

It’s been about ten months since my family and I moved to Vancouver Island and now about ten weeks since I set out to create a new collection of original paintings inspired by our new home and community. I thought it would flow easily given all the inspiration that surrounds us here from rugged shorelines, to towering ancient trees, to snowcapped mountains. In spite of this, the paintings I’ve created have fallen short of my expectations and the collection hasn’t come together. And, while it feels like a set back, I can’t compromise on this. I’m chasing a quality of light. A quality of feeling. Something to honour this incredible place and the contrast of our families transition. I hope to bring you all into this world very soon. Thank you for being here! 
.
.

A lot of folks ask me why I start with a red background. The answer is that’s it been part of my process for a long time. I always start with some sort of underpaint to make the canvas easier to paint on and because the underpaint ads depth and dimension to a finished piece. The red provides a lovely warm base that glows from behind the layers of paint that are added on top of it. The overall effect is a warm harmony, luminosity, and purposeful areas of contrast. 
.
.

Since moving to Vancouver Island, I haven’t been able to get to Whistler as much as I used to so what a treat to be back. Our family spent the long weekend biking, swimming, walking, hanging with old friends, and taking in all the incredible beauty and nature. While my little ones took an afternoon nap, I was able to sneak away to visit the lovely @adelecampbellfineart and chatted for a while with Kate. She showed me some of the incredible art and we talked about all the incredible artists represented by the gallery. It’s so easy to access, located right in the @westin_whistler, so be sure to add a stop on your next visit. Can’t wait to come back in the fall for some live painting!

It’s that time of year again 🍁 I have a new series of original fall scenes that will be released at the end of the month. This past year I have been experimenting and learning and pushing myself to try and capture what I find so compelling about this landscape. And, in the midst of an incredibly busy year for our family, our move to Vancouver island offered new opportunities and challenges for me to learn about the light and the colour and the shapes of the coast. In the studio it’s been a year marked by a lot of disappointments and frustration. Most of what I’ve created this year was never released. It just didn’t communicate my deep feelings for this incredible place. But with the arrival of fall, I’ve been doing a reset. Coming back to one of my favourite subjects has me feeling like everything is falling back into place. Everything that I find evocative and compelling about the fall and the misty landscape no matter where you are in the world has come together so beautifully in this series. The collection will release September 27th at 12pm PST to my email subscribers. Can’t wait to share! Thank you for your support! 
.
.
#Christinaclarkeartist #landscapeartist #vancouverisland #vancouver #canadianartist #contemporaryart #beautifulbc #fall #original

For all my people that love neutrals, here is a simple and beautifully calming symphony of shape and colour. I absolutely love the way this small painting draws me in to a familiar place on a quiet shoreline before nature’s giants. I feel instantly centered. 
.
Tell me, what’s one word you feel when looking at this?
.
This small original painting will release as part of a collection of fall originals on September 27th at 12pm PST to my email subscribers. Link in bio to join the list.

Finally, a series of fresh new original landscape paintings will be available next week on September 27th at 12pm PST! This collection has been a long time coming and I can’t wait to share these new pieces that celebrate autumn in the Pacific Northwest.
.
It’s been about a year exactly since our little family grew by one and we moved to Vancouver Island. And, in the midst of this incredibly busy year for our family, our move offered new opportunities and challenges for me to learn about the light, the colour, and the shapes of the coast.
.
I’ve been experimenting and learning. I’ve been pushing myself to try to capture what I find so compelling about this landscape. But, in the studio it’s been a year marked by a lot of frustration and disappointments. Most of what I created was never released. It just didn’t communicate my deep feelings for this incredible place.
.
With the arrival of fall, I’ve been doing a reset. Returning to one of my favourite seasons as a subject has me feeling like everything is falling back into place. All that I find evocative and compelling about the fall and the misty landscape here on the Pacific Northwest has come together so beautifully in this series and I’m delighted to share it with each of you.
.
Email subscribers will receive an email on September 27th at 12pm PST with access to the gallery. As always, thank you sincerely for following along and for your continued interest and support. Wishing you all a wonderful fall season!
.

I had an absolute blast painting in person at @adelecampbellfineart for the Whistler Wine Walk this past weekend. I don’t often get a chance to step outside the isolation of my studio to talk about art and my creation process so this was a real treat. Thanks to the lovely team at Adele Campbell Fine Art for welcoming me and to everyone that came by to say hi, ask thoughtful questions, look at my new work, and share some love! I appreciate all of you. I am returning home filled up and inspired!

I have worked on this painting for the better part of a year. I first started it in June as part of a collection of coastal scenes that I wanted to release to process our family’s move to Vancouver Island. I never did release that collection. Nothing I created landed for me. Nothing except this one single painting that I kept coming back to. Over the months, I picked it up, added a layer, and put it down. When I think back on the process, each new layer was added as the new experiences our family collected on the Island grew. This painting tells the story of growing into a new place and will be released as part of my holiday shop in November. If you’d like to be notified, please add your email to my collector’s list. Thank you all for being here.

Growing our family and moving to Vancouver Island has been wonderful in so many ways but I’ve struggled to find focus and balance. This tension is perhaps perfectly represented by the aesthetic diversity in my final release of the year. The Collections is a diverse body of original works that when viewed together, bridge a year’s worth of varied experiences, emotions, and seasons. Bringing them together helped me focus on the beauty we’ve been so lucky to enjoy. I sincerely hope viewing these works will bring some beauty into your life as well. The Collections gallery will release to my collector’s list on November 21st at 9am PST / 12pm EST. Thank you all for joining me!
Anyone else have impeccable timing? 🙋‍♀️ #smallbusiness #blackfriday
